<para>Java WS Core should work on any platform that supports J2SE 1.4.1 or higher. 
</para>
<para>Tested platforms for Java WS Core:</para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
    <simpara>Linux (Debian 3.1)</simpara>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <simpara>Windows XP</simpara>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <simpara>Solaris 9</simpara>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>Tested JVMs for Java WS Core:</para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
    <simpara><ulink url="http://java.sun.com/j2se/">Sun JVM</ulink> 1.4.2, 1.5.0, and 1.6.0 RC</simpara>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <simpara><ulink url="http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/java/jdk/">IBM JVM</ulink> 1.4.1, and 1.4.2</simpara>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <simpara><ulink url="http://www.bea.com/framework.jsp?CNT=index.htm&amp;FP=/content/products/jrockit">BEA JRockit JVM</ulink> 1.5.0</simpara>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>JVM notes:</para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
    <simpara><ulink url="http://gcc.gnu.org/java/">GCJ</ulink> is not supported.</simpara>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <simpara>If using IBM JVM 1.4.1 please see <ulink url="http://bugzilla.globus.org/globus/show_bug.cgi?id=2828#c4">bug 2828</ulink> for more information.</simpara>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
